Boil your #kettle{} and pour the water into a large #saucepan{} on high heat.

Add @salt{1/2%tsp}.

When boiling, stir in the @fusilli{200%g} and cook for ~{12%mins}.

Drain in a #colander{}, pop back in the saucepan, drizzle with a little @oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together. Leave to the side.

Meanwhile, trim the @courgette{1}, halve lengthways and slice into 1cm half moons.

Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1}(roughly chopped, stalks and all).

Zest and halve the @lemon{1/2}(zested and halved).

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a large #frying pan{} on high heat (no oil) and add the courgette.

Cook, until starting to brown, ~{3-4%mins} on each side.

Add the garlic and cook, stirring, for ~{1%minute}.

Once the courgettes are browned, reduce the heat and add the @creme fraiche{150%ml}, @water{100%ml} and @vegetable stock powder{1} to the frying pan.

Season with @salt{} and @salt and pepper to taste.

Stir together, bring to a simmer and cook until the sauce has thickened slightly, ~{3-4%mins}.

Stir the @king prawns{300%g} into the sauce and continue to simmer until the prawns are cooked through, ~{4-5%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

Add a splash of water if the sauce is a bit thick.

Meanwhile, mix together the lemon zest and remaining parsley in a small #bowl{}.

Toss the drained pasta into the sauce.

Add a squeeze of lemon juice to taste.

Season with salt and pepper to taste, then serve in #bowls{} topped with the lemon zest and parsley mix.

Enjoy!

> Step 5 MOD: If you've chosen to get extra prawns, just cook the recipe as instructed. The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.